			<p id="paragraph-ddd87255c8328c08867f85aa83357619">
				Clustered regularly
				<bold id="strong-bd888acd619b39d653c3bdb24c4d19ba">
					interspaced
				</bold>
				short palindromic repeats&#xA0;(CRISPR, pronounced&#xA0;crisper) are segments of&#xA0;prokaryotic&#xA0;DNA&#xA0;containing short repetitions of base sequences. Each repetition is followed by short segments of &quot;spacer DNA&quot; from previous exposures to foreign DNA (e.g a&#xA0;virus&#xA0;or&#xA0;plasmid).
			</p>
